`Queue` has a single logical consumer — once `take` returns a value, no other consumer sees it. `PubSub` is fan-out: every concurrent subscriber receives every published event. `PubSub.subscribe` returns a `Queue.Dequeue` scoped to the caller's `Scope`, so you can reuse every `Queue` API on the subscription, and when the scope closes the subscription is torn down automatically.

